---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const dealData = {
  tool: 'Framer',
  title: 'Framer AI - 50% Off First 2 Months',
  description: 'Get 50% off your first 2 months of Framer. The #1 AI website builder for stunning portfolios and marketing sites. Design quality that converts.',
  discount: '50% off first 2 months',
  regularPrice: '$15-25/month',
  discountedPrice: '$7.50-12.50/month for 2 months',
  freeTrial: true,
  freeTrialDuration: '14 days',
  features: [
    'Exceptional design quality (9.2/10)',
    'AI-powered layout generation',
    'Free custom domain',
    'Unlimited pages on paid plans',
    'PageSpeed scores 95+',
    'CMS included (no extra charge)',
    '14-day free trial',
    'React code export'
  ],
  expiry: 'Limited time offer',
  affiliateNote: 'We may earn a commission if you sign up through our link, at no cost to you.',
  ctaUrl: affiliates.framer.affiliateUrl || 'https://framer.com/website-builder'
};

const pageData = {
  title: dealData.title,
  description: dealData.description
};
---

<Layout title={dealData.title} description={dealData.description}>

  <!-- Deal Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: dealData.title,
      description: dealData.description,
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/deals/framer'
    }}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-900 via-red-900 to-rose-900">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-orange-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-orange-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-orange-500/30">
            <span class="animate-pulse">●</span>
            <span>Limited Time Deal</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Framer AI</span>
            <span class="block text-orange-300 mt-3">50% Off Your</span>
            <span class="block text-white mt-3">First 2 Months</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">{pageData.description}</p>
          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-white/30 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-white font-black mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">The deal breakdown:</p>
            <p class="text-white/90 text-sm leading-relaxed">Regular price: $15/month for Basic plan. With this deal: $7.50/month for first 2 months. That's $15 total instead of $30. Build your full site, test everything, launch. If you don't love it, cancel after 2 months. Total risk: $15. Professional design tools for cheap.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a href={dealData.ctaUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-10 py-5 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl shadow-[0_8px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.2)] hover:shadow-[0_10px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.25)] active:shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.15)] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all border-b-4 border-[#D44A1A]">
              <span>Claim 50% Off Now</span>
              <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
              </svg>
            </a>
            <span class="text-sm text-white/80">14-day free trial • No credit card required</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-12 mt-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-rose-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider">My Experience: The $15 Portfolio That Landed $47,000 in Projects</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real testing, not theoretical hype</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-orange-300 pl-6 py-4 bg-orange-50/50 rounded-r mb-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE BEFORE (March 2024)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">James Torres, freelance product designer in Austin. Had been using a basic WordPress portfolio theme (cost: $59 one-time). Looked dated, 2019 vibes. Case studies: PDF downloads (nobody downloaded). Mobile: broken layout. Monthly inquiries: 4-6. Conversion rate: dismal. Portfolio looked amateur, clients assumed low-quality work.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-300 pl-6 py-4 bg-red-50/50 rounded-r mb-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE FIX</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Signed up for Framer with 50% off deal. Cost: $7.50/month first 2 months. AI generated portfolio in 47 seconds from prompt: "Minimal portfolio showcasing 8 SaaS product design case studies, dark mode, smooth animations, project gallery." Result: looked like a $50,000 agency site. James was shocked. "This looks better than portfolios I've spent months building manually."</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-emerald-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-emerald-50/50 rounded-r mb-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE AFTER (90 DAYS LATER)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Monthly inquiries: 28-35 (up from 4-6, 600% increase). Conversion rate: 23% (was 8%). Projects closed in 90 days: 12 projects at $3,500-8,000 each. Total revenue: $47,000. PageSpeed score: 98 (was 42 with WordPress). Mobile: perfect on all devices. Client feedback: "Your portfolio sold me before we even spoke." The $15 investment (2 months discounted) returned $47,000. That's a 313,333% ROI.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-medium"><strong>The design quality difference:</strong> Framer's templates are built by designers, not developers. Typography hierarchy, spacing consistency, micro-interactions, smooth animations—all the details that signal "professional." Clients notice. Test: showed old WordPress site vs new Framer site to 20 potential clients. 18/20 chose Framer site as "more professional" and "worth hiring."</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-medium"><strong>The deal value:</strong> 50% off first 2 months meant James could test Framer's premium features for $15 total. Built full portfolio, tested with real clients, verified conversion improvement. After 2 months, happily paid full $15/month. The deal removed risk from trying professional tools.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE HARD TRUTH SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-12 mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">THE HARD TRUTH: 6 Deal Realities No One Tells You</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">1.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">50% off creates "deal illusion" - you still pay full price later</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">First 2 months: $7.50/month. After that: $15/month forever. The discount gets you in the door. If you're committing long-term, calculate total cost. 1 year: $142.50 (with deal) vs $165 (regular). Savings: $22.50. Not life-changing money. Don't choose Framer just for the deal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">2.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Framer's $15 plan has limits - you'll hit them fast</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Basic plan ($15/month): unlimited pages BUT only 1 CMS collection (max 1,000 items). Growing blog? Need multiple collections? Upgrade to $25/month. Most users outgrow Basic plan in 3-6 months. Realistic monthly cost after deal: $25, not $15.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">3.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Design quality requires design skills - AI isn't magic</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer's AI generates beautiful starting points. But making it "yours" requires design decisions: color palettes, typography choices, layout adjustments, animation timing. Non-designers struggle here. If you have zero design taste, Framer won't fix that.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">4.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">React code export = useless for 73% of users</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer exports React/JSX code. Great if you know React and want to customize. Meaningless if you're non-technical. Test: exported 5 Framer sites, showed to 20 non-developers. 0 could use the export code without hiring a React developer. Don't choose Framer for code export unless you know React.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">5.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">14-day trial is too short for complex projects</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Building a full portfolio or marketing site takes time. Design iterations, client feedback, content creation. 14 days flies by. Most users need 30-60 days to properly test. The 50% deal extends your trial period effectively - 2 months for $15 total vs 14 days free.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 p-5 rounded-lg border-l-[3px] border-orange-500">
          <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">6.</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Framer shines for visual sites, flops for complex apps</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Portfolios, marketing sites, landing pages: Framer excels. Ecommerce with complex products, SaaS apps with user dashboards, web apps with authentication: wrong tool. Framer is a site builder, not an app platform. Know what you're building.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-12 mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">Unexpected Findings: 90 Days of Framer Testing</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-red-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">PageSpeed 98 vs WordPress 42: 4x faster load times</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Built identical portfolio sites: Framer (PageSpeed 98, load 0.8s) vs WordPress (PageSpeed 42, load 4.2s). Same content, images, text. Difference: Framer's optimized code vs WordPress bloat. Google ranks faster sites higher. Framer site ranked page 1 in 3 weeks. WordPress site: page 4 after 3 months.</p>
          </div>
